{"id":14881047,"mediaExerciseId":"5044fdd6-4e5a-4ea1-8a4e-365c36092f45","exerciseName":"13","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612312,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":233,"solutions":[{"id":5985581,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This task asks to explain **how lack of transparency affect bond investors.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Transaction of bonds are privately between entities on the market, and the reporting of the transaction is little or does not exist at all. So, we can not find the bond price or the trading volume. That is behind the reason for lower transparency.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":30,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/aff1bf370891dc2443ffdabe42087c94/227ea1d30433505fd41bf9f3946aee14/lateximg_large.png","width":994},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/aff1bf370891dc2443ffdabe42087c94/227ea1d30433505fd41bf9f3946aee14/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The market dealers provide market liquidity, and the **investors accept the risk of trading activity.** Because the investors can not compare the bond's price, there is a **risk of price fluctuation**. Many securities options carry the risk that the *dealer will exploit the investors*, and if the **market provides better conditions to resell the security, the dealer will do it**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/aff1bf370891dc2443ffdabe42087c94/dff67349e4b79a2ea801397503f6b7f8/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/aff1bf370891dc2443ffdabe42087c94/dff67349e4b79a2ea801397503f6b7f8/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"*Maybe the investor can \"profit\" from this feature of the bond market by not paying the brokerage commission, but the dealer will earn anyway from a higher bid-ask spread.*","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":181,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/aff1bf370891dc2443ffdabe42087c94/ab3475b2a324c116f7c297b5248742c7/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/aff1bf370891dc2443ffdabe42087c94/ab3475b2a324c116f7c297b5248742c7/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"266889c5-d93b-4add-b867-a7f2df3473ec","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4},{"id":6381410,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"We need to infer what does lack of (bond) market transparency mean to the investors.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"As a refresher, non-transparency of the market means there are no official bonding rules nor is there a clear showing of prices and trading volume.\n\nSo, on one hand its nigh impossible to know what actual pricing nor is there any centralization, meaning investors are going in blind with what types of byers are available and what prices are present, essentially, on the outset they can only make predictions and assumptions and have to be on guard.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"On the other hand, since all buying and selling is done privately, when it comes to actual transactions investors have it more lax with numbers and deals, since there is nothing official circling over them.\n\nSo, in total, transparency makes bond trading 'finding the x on the map'. There's too much risk to go in blind without massive preparations, but if there is 'something under the x' investors can have its way with it anyway they want, assuming they are intelligent (and cunning) enough.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"6f7781b6-9de3-4e10-ad20-c46d051bb286","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881048,"exerciseName":"14","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a8a0a30f-3f41-4ff6-9c4e-bb4649e034a0","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-14-a8a0a30f-3f41-4ff6-9c4e-bb4649e034a0"},{"id":14881049,"exerciseName":"15","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ba90aa4e-06c6-40e1-b292-d1fa1bd9d680","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-15-ba90aa4e-06c6-40e1-b292-d1fa1bd9d680"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881046,"exerciseName":"12","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a322f2d2-d5bc-438c-8d5e-a37cde8cf5fb","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-12-a322f2d2-d5bc-438c-8d5e-a37cde8cf5fb"},{"id":14881045,"exerciseName":"11","page":232,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"cfe24fe5-37b8-4e02-a060-a4f31655013e","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-11-cfe24fe5-37b8-4e02-a060-a4f31655013e"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-13-5044fdd6-4e5a-4ea1-8a4e-365c36092f45"}